About the Keeper of the Scrolls



My name is Mike (not too exciting, is it? 😴), and I am the Curator of this collection, I am The Seeker and Keeper of the Pika Scrolls of Power.

Some have said I'm following in the footsteps of the explorers, speakers, and teachers before me. My life has been a relentless expedition, not for golden idols, but for scattered truths.

I am a Shibarium Knight, a guardian of the Pika people's true wealth: the knowledge of self-sovereignty.

This calling wasn't a choice; it was an instinct, a reaction to a world full of fake prophets and get-rich-quick schemes I first encountered in the 1990s. I saw the empty promises of motivational speakers and MLM gurus who sold systems but never taught skills. They sold the dream but hid the blueprint. I’ve hated their brand of false hope ever since.

My own journey was that of the prodigal son. I came from a world of intelligent, good-hearted people who didn't understand the brutal realities of business or personal power. Their kindness was a vulnerability, and I inherited it, becoming a people-pleaser who sacrificed his own path to keep others comfortable. It led me through years of struggle, depression, and association with people who, while family, operated on a frequency that was not my own.

My enlightenment didn't come from a university. It was forged in meditation, in quiet observation, in the gut-wrenching analysis of my own failures, and in the raw honesty of discussions with others on the path.

The great tragedy of modern life is that the knowledge we need to succeed is scattered. It’s in pieces. A guru teaches you to be confident, but not how to build a sales script. A mentor tells you to "hustle," but not how to confront the inner weakness that makes you procrastinate. They coddle you. They focus on surface-level remedies because the truth is uncomfortable: you must know who you are, confront your deficiencies, and master the fundamental laws of power and human interaction.

My mandate as Curator is clear:

To Gather the Scrolls: To relentlessly read, observe, experiment, and interact to discover the scattered pieces of wisdom.

To Preserve the Codex: To catalog this knowledge in a way that connects the mental, the physical, and the spiritual—the three pillars of true power that most teachings ignore.

To Grant Access: This knowledge does not belong to me. All public domain materials here are marked "PCG" (Perpetual Copyrights Granted). You are free to learn from it, add to it, remix it, and resell it. This is how the knowledge survives and grows.

I am not a leader you are meant to follow. I am a curator who maintains the armory. My only job is to ensure these scrolls are here for those who need them, long after I am gone. That is why they reside on these free platforms, safe from hosting fees and the whims of future owners.

The path to your own power is within these scrolls. Learn, grow, lead, serve, and contribute.
